title: For Sale/Trade:  Nigerian Scammer Alert :)
postcontent:
REDACTED  

Just a heads up to other sellers... the above email address contacted me wanting to buy a DPMS rifle I have listed here. Never mentioned the item name, wanted to pay with a cashiers check, wanted the listing removed, strange wording, etc... 

"Thanks for contacting me. I must confess that I am so interested in purchasing this. I am sorry for replying a little late. I am away for a family emergency. I love the picture and really want to buy. Is that the final price? I understand if you are not willing to go down. 

  However, because I am away and really not sure of when i will be in town, I want it shipped to me. I will get a FFL so that transmission can be through FFL and you know I am not possessing this illegally. Lets discuss on the payment. I am ready to have a check sent to you. A cashiers check will be sent to you. When the funds is in your account, we can then proceed on the shipment. 

Let me have your   FULL NAME,ADDRESS and phone number.  these details are needed for the check.

Feel free to text me on    REDACTED if need be

Please understand that I am making this arrangement because I want to purchase this before any other person and I am also willing to pay the shipping fees.

If everything looks good, Please send me the details and then kindly delete the post on the site for it is now mine...lol

Get back to me as soon as you can."

The kicker was what he emailed me this evening.... "Ogbeni park well"

WTF?! A quick search for the phrase takes me to a page covering Nigerian Pidgin English phrases. Shocker. 
Anyway, beware of these scams :)
